+# Exploration 002 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Resolve the Step-4 ambiguity in `Delayed-Threshold Itinerary` without changing
+the frozen packet object, finite window, sign sheet, or threshold language. The
+specific question is whether the Step-2 itinerary candidate honestly splits
+into:
+
+- `pre-trigger delay filter`
+- `next-stage transfer-start filter`
+
+or whether one or both notions must be discarded.
+
+## Method
+
+1. Reconstruct the original Step-2 itinerary criterion from the cited local
+   materials.
+2. Separate the clauses into early delayed-trigger logic and late transfer
+   logic, if the fixed event language permits that separation.
+3. Test the candidate split against the inherited Step-4 dossier:
+   `F_DT(delta, eta)`, `F_SS(mu)`, and `F_SL(rho)`.
+4. Record which split notions survive, fail, or must be discarded, and explain
+   the earned reason.
+5. Check whether any surviving notion has a concrete downstream gate.
+
+## Running Notes
+
+### Initial setup
+
+- Created the report skeleton before reading source material, per the explorer
+  instructions.
+

